1. Build the striped_base docker image:

    $ docker build -t striped_base --no-cache striped_base
    
2. Build the micro server image:

    $ docker build -t micro_server --no-cache micro_server
    
3. Run the micro_server:

    $ docker run --rm -p 8765:8765 micro_server
    
4. Point your client code to the node where you run the microserver. It has to be inside FNAL LAN:

    from striped.job import SinglePointStripedSession as Session
    job_server = ("node.where.docker.runs.fnal.gov", 8765)
    session = Session(job_server) 
    ...
    


